In the Matter of Samuel J. ECKHAUS, Bankrupt; John L. Lyttle, as Trustee, etc., Petitioner. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. December 17, 1926.) No. 150. See, also, 14 F.(2d) 471. Emanuel M. Kaiser, of New York City, for petitioner. Joseph W. Gottlieb, of Brooklyn, N. Y., for respondent Yawnick.

Before HOUGH, MANTON, and MACK, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Order reversed in open ' court.
